Motorists are queueing as one of the lanes is closed in order for the emergency services to assist those involved in the accident. It is still unknown if anyone was injured. The lane is closed between junctions 16 and 15, with delays until junction 17 for Maple Cross. National Highways has said that delays reach about 40 minutes. The crash occurred anticlockwise on the highway, between junction 16 and 15. Meanwhile, congestion is also reported on the M3 eastbound between junctions J3 and J2. National Highways suggests the delay is approximately 30 minutes. The accident happened early in the afternoon on Monday, but delays went on until after 15.30pm. National Highways has said the road is expected to clear between 16.30 and 16.45pm.  More to follow...